### 5. APPLICATION DATA SHAPE (Accepted Applications)

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/integrations/supabase/types.ts`**

**campaign_applications table (Lines 184-241):**
```typescript
Row {
  id: string;
  campaign_id: string;
  creator_id: string;
  status: "pending" | "accepted" | "rejected" | "completed";
  proposed_price: number | null;
  proposal: string | null;
  ai_match_score: number | null;
  created_at: string | null;
  updated_at: string | null;
}
```

**Joined campaign data from campaigns table (Lines 305-375):**
```typescript
Row {
  title: string;           // Campaign title
  budget: number | null;
  description: string | null;
  deliverables: string[] | null;
  brand_id: string;        // Campaign creator (Brand)
  deadline: string | null;
  platforms: string[] | null;
  industry: string | null;
  requirements: string | null;
}
```

**Creator profile data (via JOIN with profiles + creator_profiles):**
- From profiles table: `display_name`, `handle`, `email`, `avatar_url`
- From creator_profiles table: `follower_count`, `engagement_rate`, `creator_types`, `portfolio_url`, `social_links`

**How applications are queried (CampaignApplicationsDialog.tsx Lines 31-40):**
```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from("campaign_applications")
  .select("*, creator_profiles(*, profiles(*))")
  .eq("campaign_id", campaign.id)
  .order("created_at", { ascending: false });
```

**Key fields on accepted application:**
- `proposed_price` - The price creator proposed (line 160 in CampaignApplicationsDialog)
- `creator_id` - Links to creator
- `campaign_id` - Links to campaign with all campaign details
- `proposal` - Creator's written proposal
- Creator name: `application.creator_profiles?.profiles?.display_name`

